28
00:01:06,330 --> 00:01:09,030
of stock at an agreed-upon price on

29
00:01:09,030 --> 00:01:10,670
or before a particular date.

30
00:01:11,370 --> 00:01:13,270
And a put option is the same thing,

31
00:01:13,650 --> 00:01:15,550
except it gives the option holder the right

32
00:01:15,550 --> 00:01:17,610
to sell shares of stock at an agreed

33
00:01:17,610 --> 00:01:20,270
-upon price on or before a particular date.

34
00:01:21,070 --> 00:01:23,690
And the agreed-upon price is what we

35
00:01:23,690 --> 00:01:26,690
refer to as the strike price, and the

36
00:01:26,690 --> 00:01:29,010
particular date is what we refer to as

37
00:01:29,010 --> 00:01:31,150
the option's expiration date.

38
00:01:32,290 --> 00:01:33,850
Now, we got those out of the way,

39
00:01:33,930 --> 00:01:36,190
but in layman's terms, let's say you bought

