Yes, this is true, but let's quickly look

273
00:10:35,410 --> 00:10:36,630
at one more scenario.

274
00:10:37,330 --> 00:10:39,510
In this scenario, the stock goes down.

275
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:42,690
It moves down to let's say $100 per

276
00:10:42,690 --> 00:10:43,030
share.

277
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:46,370
Now remember, you own the 125 strike call

278
00:10:46,370 --> 00:10:49,130
option that you bought for $500, and this

279
00:10:49,130 --> 00:10:50,890
call option gives you the right to buy

280
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:53,370
stock at $125 per share.

281
00:10:53,730 --> 00:10:56,070
But why on earth would anyone want to

282
00:10:56,070 --> 00:10:58,650
purchase stock at $125 if the stock is

283
00:10:58,650 --> 00:10:59,810
currently at $100?

284
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:03,150
The answer is you wouldn't, and thankfully you

285
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:03,790
don't have to.

286
00:11:04,190 --> 00:11:06,470
Let's think back to the definition of a

287
00:11:06,470 --> 00:11:07,050
call option.

288
00:11:07,890 --> 00:11:10,150
It gives you the right, but not the

289
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:12,130
obligation to buy stock.

290
00:11:12,850 --> 00:11:15,810
So owning this call option doesn't require you

291
00:11:15,810 --> 00:11:17,810
to buy stock if you don't want to.

292
00:11:18,190 --> 00:11:20,490
And of course, you aren't going to exercise

293
00:11:20,490 --> 00:11:23,310
your right to buy stock at $125 if

294
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:25,490
the current market price is cheaper than that.

295
00:11:26,150 --> 00:11:27,870
So in this case, you simply lost the

296
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:30,290
premium you paid for the option, which was

297
00:11:30,290 --> 00:11:30,870
$500.

298
00:11:31,710 --> 00:11:33,750
If you would have bought stock at $125

299
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:37,450
instead, you would currently be down $2,500.

300
00:11:38,430 --> 00:11:40,770
So that's the benefit of buying an option

301
00:11:40,770 --> 00:11:42,590
rather than just buying the stock.

302
00:11:42,930 --> 00:11:45,190
You can put up much less capital, and

303
00:11:45,190 --> 00:11:46,870
therefore have much less risk.

304
00:11:47,230 --> 00:11:49,510
But in exchange for that, you will have

305
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:51,070
to pay a premium for it.

306
00:11:51,950 --> 00:11:53,870
And by the way, you can also trade

307
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:55,790
put options in this way as well.

308
00:11:56,190 --> 00:11:58,630
If you buy a put option without already

309
00:11:58,630 --> 00:12:00,870
owning shares of stock, then you are simply

310
00:12:00,870 --> 00:12:02,810
betting that the stock will go down.

311
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:06,030
Because if you exercise your right to sell

312
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:08,310
stock that you don't own, then you will

313
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:10,430
just end up with a short stock position.

314
00:12:11,390 --> 00:12:13,930
So again, if you buy a call, you

315
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:15,470
are betting that the stock is going to

316
00:12:15,470 --> 00:12:16,050
go up.

317
00:12:16,530 --> 00:12:17,950
And if you buy a put, you are

318
00:12:17,950 --> 00:12:19,470
betting that the stock is going to go

319
00:12:19,470 --> 00:12:19,850
down.

320
00:12:20,590 --> 00:12:22,130
Now before you go out and start buying

321
00:12:22,130 --> 00:12:23,790
calls on every stock you think is going

322
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:25,610
to go up, and puts on every stock

323
00:12:25,610 --> 00:12:27,630
you think is going to go down, keep

324
00:12:27,630 --> 00:12:29,990
watching because there are big negatives to buying

325
00:12:29,990 --> 00:12:30,930
options like this.

326
00:12:31,330 --> 00:12:32,710
And of course, we are going to show

327
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,950
you much better ways to trade options.

328
00:12:35,910 --> 00:12:37,930
One last note before moving on, you don't

329
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:40,870
actually have to exercise your option contracts when

330
00:12:40,870 --> 00:12:42,670
you trade them like we showed you in

331
00:12:42,670 --> 00:12:43,190
the examples.

332
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:46,070
You can simply buy an option and then

333
00:12:46,070 --> 00:12:48,150
sell the option, hopefully at a higher price

334
00:12:48,150 --> 00:12:48,930
than you bought it for.

335
